Uh, what do you say we go home
and see what happens?

22:43.029 --> 22:44.628
Yeah, it's starting to rain
in here.

22:44.630 --> 22:47.031
Mm-hm.

22:47.033 --> 22:48.666
- It's the DeLoreans.
- Okay, okay.

22:48.668 --> 22:50.234
[clears throat]

22:50.236 --> 22:52.136
Thank you so much
for a lovely evening.

22:52.138 --> 22:54.705
Oh, thank you. It was lovely
to finally have you over.

22:54.707 --> 22:56.374
- It's a beautiful house.
- Oh, thanks.

22:56.376 --> 22:57.875
- Really. Absolutely.
- Jim, right?

22:57.877 --> 22:59.643
- Yes, sir.
- Bill Mercer.

22:59.645 --> 23:02.646
Vice president of whatever
the fuck he has me doing next.

23:02.648 --> 23:04.548
- That's my wife, Ellen.
- Hi.

23:04.550 --> 23:05.816
Why don't you
join us downstairs?

23:05.818 --> 23:06.917
We're just lettin'
our hair down,

23:06.919 --> 23:08.152
now that the pressure's off.

23:08.154 --> 23:09.720
Oh, yeah. Uh-- uh,
that'd be great.

23:09.722 --> 23:12.089
- You're okay with that, right?
- Yeah, fine.

23:12.091 --> 23:13.324
I'll see you tonight.

23:13.326 --> 23:16.026
[chuckling]

23:16.028 --> 23:18.896
That husband of yours
is quite the charmer.

23:18.898 --> 23:20.765
Only until you get to know him.

23:20.767 --> 23:24.034
After tonight,
we have 175 dealers signed up.

23:24.036 --> 23:25.936
That's $25,000 each,

23:25.938 --> 23:28.572
plus a commitment to take
100 cars in the first year.

23:28.574 --> 23:30.608
It needs to be 250, 300.

23:30.610 --> 23:32.476
We'll get there, John.
It's a done deal.

23:35.715 --> 23:37.782
- Nice shot.
- He-he-he.

23:39.352 --> 23:41.118
You serve.

23:41.120 --> 23:42.753
What so funny?

23:42.755 --> 23:46.557
Guys, I've been around,
I know when I'm being pitched.

23:46.559 --> 23:49.393
Uh-- uh, look, I-- I-- I know
I'm living in a nice house

23:49.395 --> 23:51.262
in a swanky neighborhood,
but, uh,

23:51.264 --> 23:53.197
I'm behind on the rent
and I don't know

23:53.199 --> 23:54.865
where next month's is coming
from, so if you're looking

23:54.867 --> 23:57.268
for an investment from me,
you might be, uh...

23:57.270 --> 23:58.702
Well, you're barking
up the wrong tree.

23:58.704 --> 24:00.871
[tapping bat]

24:00.873 --> 24:02.373
Well, fuck you then. [chuckles]

24:03.476 --> 24:04.775
[chuckles]

24:04.777 --> 24:06.777
[indistinct chatter on TV]

24:13.386 --> 24:15.453
[all laughing]

24:17.890 --> 24:21.091
If you're runnin' low on cash,
maybe you'd like to earn some.

24:21.093 --> 24:23.961
- Ooh. Ooh-ooh.
- Oh?

24:23.963 --> 24:28.098
Sure, I'm always up
for a little table tennis.

24:28.100 --> 24:30.401
You mean, ping-pong?

24:30.403 --> 24:32.403
Yeah. I call it table tennis.

24:32.405 --> 24:33.804
Jim, it's ping-pong.

24:35.241 --> 24:36.941
Alright.

24:36.943 --> 24:40.077
Alright, 50 bucks if you can
take a point off me.

24:40.079 --> 24:42.446
Hmm, I believe I might be

24:42.448 --> 24:45.182
getting hustled here, sir, huh?

24:45.184 --> 24:46.750
How do you hold this thing?
Is this right?

24:46.752 --> 24:48.486
- Yeah, exactly like that.
- Am I doing this right?

24:48.488 --> 24:50.488
Stop fuckin' around, come on.

24:50.490 --> 24:52.256
Bill: Alright, John.

24:52.258 --> 24:53.657
Alright.

24:53.659 --> 24:56.660
[ball clacking]

25:06.439 --> 25:07.838
Ooh!

25:14.113 --> 25:15.980
[instrumental music]

25:15.982 --> 25:17.448
Uh-oh.

25:21.687 --> 25:25.055
Oh, no, John, John, come on.
Don't worry about it.

25:25.057 --> 25:28.158
I mean, hell,
it's only table tennis, right?

25:28.160 --> 25:30.361
Let me walk you out.

25:32.331 --> 25:35.032
You know, Jim, I'm sorry
you're havin' a hard time.

25:35.034 --> 25:38.035
And if there's anything I can do
to help, you let me know.

25:38.037 --> 25:40.504
Oh, yeah. No, I mean,
I got a few things cookin'.

25:40.506 --> 25:42.039
But, uh, I mean,
it should all work out,

25:42.041 --> 25:43.641
but thank you for the thought.

25:43.643 --> 25:45.743
Ah, that's what friends are for.

25:45.745 --> 25:47.144
Yeah.

25:49.882 --> 25:53.083
You know,
the thing about ping-pong...

25:53.085 --> 25:54.885
When the game
first came to America

25:54.887 --> 25:57.021
it was trademarked ping-pong
by these guys,

25:57.023 --> 25:58.489
the Parker Brothers.

25:58.491 --> 26:00.991
And they kept a strict control
over that name,

26:00.993 --> 26:03.894
but it still made it
into the lexicon.

26:03.896 --> 26:05.563
It's not a car.

26:05.565 --> 26:07.565
It's not a sports car.

26:09.001 --> 26:10.401
It's a DeLorean.

26:11.103 --> 26:13.037
Hmm.

26:13.039 --> 26:14.672
Yeah.

26:14.674 --> 26:16.640
You don't hang out much,
do you?

26:17.577 --> 26:19.009
Well, uh...

26:19.011 --> 26:21.445
[chuckles]

26:21.447 --> 26:23.013
- I travel a lot. I do.
- Yeah.

26:23.015 --> 26:24.582
Hey, speakin' of which,
do you want me

26:24.584 --> 26:26.884
to keep an eye on the house
when you guys are gone?

26:26.886 --> 26:28.552
You know,
like clean the pool or...

26:28.554 --> 26:30.087
This area probably
turns into a jungle--

26:30.089 --> 26:32.456
Well, that would be, um...

26:32.458 --> 26:34.291
Alright, I-- I can arrange
payment.

26:34.293 --> 26:35.960
No, no, John, John, come on.

26:35.962 --> 26:37.394
You don't have to pay me.

26:37.396 --> 26:39.196
Really. It's okay.

26:39.198 --> 26:41.398
Thank you, Jim.

26:41.400 --> 26:43.934
Hey, that's what
friends are for.

26:47.807 --> 26:49.540
I'm kidding, come here.

26:51.143 --> 26:52.543
There it is.

26:54.046 --> 26:56.080
Friends hug.

26:56.082 --> 26:58.716
Alright, uh, please tell
Cristina thank you

26:58.718 --> 27:00.050
from both me and Ellen.

27:03.289 --> 27:06.290
[instrumental music]

27:18.170 --> 27:20.004
Check, check, check.

27:31.083 --> 27:33.917
<i> Jim: Hi, I was looking</i>
<i> for Morgan.</i>

27:33.919 --> 27:36.887
- Who wants to know?
- Jim. Jim Hoffman.

27:37.757 --> 27:38.756
I'll go check.

27:40.593 --> 27:42.526
[recorder malfunctioning]
Check, check, check, check...

27:42.528 --> 27:43.827
What?

27:43.829 --> 27:45.696
- What's that?
- Check.

27:45.698 --> 27:48.198
Please go check, yeah.
Thank you.

27:48.200 --> 27:49.233
Alright.

27:54.340 --> 27:57.107
[dramatic music]

28:06.686 --> 28:08.652
[clears throat]

28:08.654 --> 28:10.954
- He says, come on in.
- Oh, well, I mean, you know...

28:10.956 --> 28:12.489
If he's busy, I can always come
back another time.

28:12.491 --> 28:13.957
Morgan: Get in here!

28:13.959 --> 28:15.359
Okay, yeah.

28:22.568 --> 28:24.568
Jim Hoffman.

28:26.572 --> 28:29.339
Hey, Morgan, hi.

28:29.341 --> 28:31.809
- Long time, Jim.
- Uh, the place looks great.

28:31.811 --> 28:33.077
You know, so do you.

28:34.380 --> 28:36.513
Um, so, you still flyin'?

28:36.515 --> 28:38.716
Where's my three million bucks?

28:38.718 --> 28:40.918
Come on, Morgan,
we talked about this, okay?

28:40.920 --> 28:43.520
- You know what happened.
- Well, I thought I did.

28:43.522 --> 28:45.723
- And then you disappeared.
- I... No, I... No.

28:45.725 --> 28:48.192
No, I didn't disappear.
No, no, I-- I just, you know,

28:48.194 --> 28:50.260
I had to lie low for a while.
But I'm not hiding.

28:50.262 --> 28:52.663
I wasn't, you know.
We're in the phonebook.

28:52.665 --> 28:54.832
So, it's, yeah,
at least had to

28:54.834 --> 28:57.401
go straight, you know for the...
for the family, so...

28:57.403 --> 28:59.069
I'm-- I'm now doing some
consulting work

28:59.071 --> 29:00.437
now with John DeLorean.

29:00.439 --> 29:02.106
You know, the car guy?

29:02.108 --> 29:04.408
So, he's makin'
this amazing car.

