34:38.911 --> 34:41.912
Howard: James D'Jong.

34:41.914 --> 34:44.014
Or is it D'Yong?

34:44.016 --> 34:48.085
- This is your birth name?
- Mm-hmm.

34:48.087 --> 34:52.889
Is your wife even aware
that you are James D'Jong?

34:52.891 --> 34:54.391
I mean, I think so. I-- I...

34:54.393 --> 34:57.294
I actually don't know
if it's ever come up.

34:57.296 --> 35:00.730
And what about Mr. DeLorean,
was he aware of your real name?

35:00.732 --> 35:02.632
Your checkered history?

35:02.634 --> 35:04.534
- I believe he was.
- You believe?

35:04.536 --> 35:07.971
- You-- you discussed it?
James: No, but I alluded to it.

35:07.973 --> 35:10.407
One of his executives
had me background checked.

35:10.409 --> 35:13.610
Background check on a man
who has no criminal history,

35:13.612 --> 35:15.278
never spent a night in prison,

35:15.280 --> 35:18.315
has only filed one
somewhat suspect tax return

35:18.317 --> 35:19.983
in the last ten years?

35:19.985 --> 35:22.385
What background was there
to check?

35:22.387 --> 35:24.754
James D'jong on the other
hand...

35:24.756 --> 35:29.326
Well, one can see why you might
wanna change your name.

35:29.962 --> 35:31.294
Hmm.

35:36.502 --> 35:39.402
Oh, don't worry about him.

35:39.404 --> 35:43.240
He's just antsy because
we're stalled on the money.

35:43.242 --> 35:44.341
What're you talkin' about?
I thought you guys were

35:44.343 --> 35:45.642
signin' 'em up left and right.

35:45.644 --> 35:46.910
Not gonna raise 90 million

35:46.912 --> 35:49.913
with penny antique
car dealerships.

35:49.915 --> 35:52.582
GM thinks they've created
a monster and it scares them.

35:54.186 --> 35:57.087
If Detroit is scared of you,
so is corporate America.

35:59.525 --> 36:02.025
The fact is, I don't think
I've got a chance in hell

36:02.027 --> 36:04.027
of raising 90 million.

36:05.797 --> 36:07.297
So take it somewhere else.

36:07.299 --> 36:09.599
Just like that, right?

36:09.601 --> 36:11.001
I'm being serious.

36:12.704 --> 36:13.837
Look, John...

36:15.707 --> 36:18.041
Roy digs deep enough

36:18.043 --> 36:20.177
he's probably gonna find
something you're not gonna like.

36:22.548 --> 36:24.481
Truth is, I've flown

36:24.483 --> 36:26.883
all kinds of shit
all over the world.

36:26.885 --> 36:30.887
Bangkok, Bolivia...
There're all types of people.

36:32.991 --> 36:36.393
The one thing I've learned is
that there is a deal to be made

36:36.395 --> 36:38.461
everywhere, always.

36:40.199 --> 36:42.332
Right now we might be livin' in,

36:42.334 --> 36:44.167
oh, sad cynical times,

36:44.169 --> 36:47.270
but you're the goddamn
American dream, man.

36:48.540 --> 36:51.808
People around the world
love that shit.

36:51.810 --> 36:54.477
So I say, you know,
they don't love you here...

36:54.479 --> 36:56.413
just, uh, take it
somewhere they will.

36:56.415 --> 36:58.448
Bring the American dream
to them.

37:03.755 --> 37:07.657
It's an entire Atlantic ocean
away from your primary market

37:07.659 --> 37:10.594
and it's in the middle
of a fucking warzone.

37:10.596 --> 37:11.895
Do you know
how many people were killed

37:11.897 --> 37:15.565
in Northern Ireland last year?
Ninety.

37:15.567 --> 37:18.235
Do you know how many people
were murdered in Detroit?

37:18.237 --> 37:19.669
Nine hundred!

37:19.671 --> 37:20.870
Do the fucking math.

37:20.872 --> 37:23.573
You'd be starting from scratch.

37:23.575 --> 37:26.543
The last thing they built
was the Titanic.

37:26.545 --> 37:28.745
Man on TV: It's
John DeLorean's new sports car,

37:28.747 --> 37:30.413
the DMC12.

37:30.415 --> 37:32.415
Thirty thousand a year,
the production target

37:32.417 --> 37:34.384
for the Northern Ireland plant,

37:34.386 --> 37:37.687
with the first cars
to go to dealers this fall.

37:37.689 --> 37:39.055
Oh! What's wrong?

37:39.057 --> 37:41.057
Is your little buddy
in a faraway land

37:41.059 --> 37:43.360
and can't come out and play?

37:43.362 --> 37:45.228
Mm-hmm.

37:45.230 --> 37:47.230
It think it's cute how you
always gets sad

37:47.232 --> 37:48.531
when he's out of town.

37:48.533 --> 37:50.033
Oh, come on.

37:50.035 --> 37:51.301
Man on TV: The British
government spent

37:51.303 --> 37:54.104
$120 million
for the plant.

37:54.106 --> 37:56.773
For John DeLorean,
it's the realization of a dream

37:56.775 --> 37:59.876
that started a long time ago.

37:59.878 --> 38:01.811
<i> Howard: So for 18 months,</i>

38:01.813 --> 38:06.082
