39:34.005 --> 39:36.740
Gravestones and marbles.

39:36.742 --> 39:38.308
You do know
marbles aren't made of marble,

39:38.310 --> 39:41.211
they're made of glass.

39:41.213 --> 39:42.579
I don't know that.
I had no idea. I-- I didn't...

39:42.581 --> 39:43.680
I didn't know that.

39:43.682 --> 39:45.382
What would I do without you?

39:45.384 --> 39:47.917
I would run around
sounding like a dipshit.

39:47.919 --> 39:50.053
Hey, look, baby. You know,
you got to realize something.

39:50.055 --> 39:51.821
In the America that I grew up in

39:51.823 --> 39:54.324
a man was defined
by the work that he did.

39:54.326 --> 39:57.093
But it never stopped me
from dreaming, okay?

39:58.697 --> 40:00.363
When I was nine months old,
my daddy

40:00.365 --> 40:02.365
bought me a beat up,
old Chevrolet.

40:02.367 --> 40:05.602
He broke it down
to 42,000 pieces

40:05.604 --> 40:08.605
and I put it together
with my hands and my tool.

40:08.607 --> 40:11.841
My tool! What? What? What?

40:11.843 --> 40:14.811
[instrumental music]

40:21.253 --> 40:23.086
John: I know
it's incredibly complicated,

40:23.088 --> 40:24.554
but you just have to trust me.

40:24.556 --> 40:26.122
Molly: I do trust you,
but then...

40:26.124 --> 40:27.757
