1:20:12.241 --> 1:20:13.808
I think you're just
stringing us along

1:20:13.810 --> 1:20:15.409
'cause you're a fuckin'
chinless fake.

1:20:15.411 --> 1:20:18.012
- Cut the shit!
- Hmm?

1:20:18.014 --> 1:20:19.580
I was worried
you would fuck it up.

1:20:19.582 --> 1:20:21.782
- Me?
- Morgan thinks you're a snake.

1:20:21.784 --> 1:20:23.651
Morgan. Oh, yeah...
What, you talked to Morgan?

1:20:23.653 --> 1:20:25.319
I talk to everyone,
that's what I do.

1:20:25.321 --> 1:20:27.421
- Okay.
- You fucked him over.

1:20:27.423 --> 1:20:29.690
Oh, okay.
That's what he told you, huh?

1:20:29.692 --> 1:20:31.859
You guys have little chit-chats
and everything now?

1:20:31.861 --> 1:20:33.661
That's good. Well, did he...

1:20:33.663 --> 1:20:35.162
Did he tell you about him
and Cristina?

1:20:35.164 --> 1:20:36.497
- Did that come up?
- Excuse me?

1:20:36.499 --> 1:20:37.798
Oh...

1:20:37.800 --> 1:20:40.134
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.
See. No, she...

1:20:40.136 --> 1:20:42.636
Well, Morgan used to work
for this millionaire

1:20:42.638 --> 1:20:47.107
that, that Cristina used to,
uh, see, like, date, or, uh...

1:20:47.109 --> 1:20:48.142
Or how do you put it?

1:20:48.144 --> 1:20:49.710
[groans]

1:20:49.712 --> 1:20:52.213
What the fuck are you saying
about my wife?

1:20:52.215 --> 1:20:53.280
[phone ringing]

1:20:53.282 --> 1:20:55.516
I, nothing... Nothing.

1:20:56.185 --> 1:20:57.618
I...

1:20:57.620 --> 1:20:59.587
[ringing continues]

1:21:04.126 --> 1:21:06.393
John: Hello?
- Uh...

1:21:06.395 --> 1:21:07.595
[sighs]

1:21:09.498 --> 1:21:11.465
Well, I can't thank you enough.

1:21:14.637 --> 1:21:16.837
John, I'm sorry.

1:21:16.839 --> 1:21:18.572
I'm sorry,
I shouldn't have said that.

1:21:18.574 --> 1:21:20.407
I... Well...

1:21:20.409 --> 1:21:23.210
It's probably for the best this
whole thing's falling apart.

1:21:24.547 --> 1:21:27.147
That was James Benedict
at Davrow.

1:21:29.018 --> 1:21:31.552
He's gonna loan me
two million dollars.

1:21:31.554 --> 1:21:34.488
[dramatic music]

1:21:35.925 --> 1:21:37.725
Morgan just took off.

1:21:39.028 --> 1:21:40.995
[crickets chirping]

1:21:43.399 --> 1:21:45.599
Man on TV: With his firm,
and all the remaining jobs

1:21:45.601 --> 1:21:48.102
that depend on it
on the brink of extinction,

1:21:48.104 --> 1:21:50.170
DeLorean, a former
General Motors executive

1:21:50.172 --> 1:21:51.872
vowed to fight on.

1:21:51.874 --> 1:21:54.074
John on TV: The company's going
to survive as long as

1:21:54.076 --> 1:21:55.743
I have a breath left in me.

1:21:55.745 --> 1:21:58.279
[phone ringing]

1:21:58.281 --> 1:22:00.381
Man on TV: Up until now,

1:22:00.383 --> 1:22:02.616
the bank rolled DeLorean's plant
here at Belfast...

1:22:02.618 --> 1:22:04.051
Hoffman residence.

1:22:04.053 --> 1:22:05.486
Yeah. Morgan.

1:22:06.589 --> 1:22:08.622
Okay. Yeah.
No, sounds good.

1:22:08.624 --> 1:22:10.791
I'm on my way. Alright.

1:22:10.793 --> 1:22:12.426
Man on TV: ...whether they'll
continue to bail out

1:22:12.428 --> 1:22:15.396
the firm that bears
John DeLorean's name.

1:22:15.398 --> 1:22:16.463
Let it sink.

1:22:16.465 --> 1:22:19.466
[music continues]

1:22:20.970 --> 1:22:22.369
Morgan: You look nervous.

1:22:22.371 --> 1:22:24.538
Jim: Yeah,
'cause I am fucking nervous.

1:22:25.474 --> 1:22:26.874
Where's the stuff?

1:22:26.876 --> 1:22:28.943
I told you,
it's in the car with Katy.

1:22:28.945 --> 1:22:30.311
Yeah, well, I hope,
there's some left.

1:22:30.313 --> 1:22:31.879
You better hurry.

1:22:32.949 --> 1:22:34.048
Hey.

1:22:34.917 --> 1:22:36.283
Hey, gorgeous.

1:22:37.486 --> 1:22:39.920
[clears throat]
Hey, lifesaver.

1:22:39.922 --> 1:22:41.555
- Hey.
- Let's show him.

1:22:42.558 --> 1:22:43.991
Uh-hmm.

1:22:58.174 --> 1:22:59.640
- Holy moly!
- Mm-hm.

1:22:59.642 --> 1:23:00.674
[Morgan chuckling]

1:23:00.676 --> 1:23:02.076
[engine sputtering]

1:23:03.813 --> 1:23:04.979
Holy moly!

1:23:05.781 --> 1:23:08.949
[tires screeching]

1:23:08.951 --> 1:23:11.285
[engines revving]

1:23:11.287 --> 1:23:12.486
[tires screeching]

1:23:14.123 --> 1:23:17.291
Morgan Hetrick, Katy Connors,
you're under arrest.

1:23:17.293 --> 1:23:19.093
Morgan:
Motherfucking mother fucker!

1:23:19.095 --> 1:23:20.861
- Step away from the car.
- Morgan...

1:23:20.863 --> 1:23:23.831
How'd he... How does he...
How does he know me?

1:23:23.833 --> 1:23:25.599
You fucker!

1:23:25.601 --> 1:23:27.167
- I'm going to fuckin' kill you!
Katy: Get the fuck away from me!

1:23:27.169 --> 1:23:28.836
You're fuckin' dead, Hoffman!

1:23:28.838 --> 1:23:30.104
You're dead!

1:23:30.106 --> 1:23:31.672
[laughing] Oh, yeah!

1:23:31.674 --> 1:23:33.040
Fucked me twice...

1:23:33.042 --> 1:23:36.010
Fucked me twice...
Ow! Okay, fuckhead!

1:23:36.012 --> 1:23:37.344
Yeah. You too.

1:23:37.346 --> 1:23:39.046
You'll pay, assholes!

1:23:39.048 --> 1:23:40.781
- Don't say a word, baby!
- Don't push me. I'm going.

1:23:40.783 --> 1:23:43.017
Morgan:
Don't say a fuckin' word!

1:23:43.019 --> 1:23:45.285
I thought you were my
fuckin' friend.

1:23:45.287 --> 1:23:46.920
You're dead, Hoffman!

1:23:47.723 --> 1:23:49.223
[Morgan laughing]

1:23:49.225 --> 1:23:53.560
Oh, you, motherfuck!
Watch the fuckin' hat!

1:23:53.562 --> 1:23:54.595
[car door closes]

1:23:59.035 --> 1:24:00.701
One down, one to go.

1:24:04.573 --> 1:24:05.939
Hey, Jim.

1:24:07.510 --> 1:24:08.876
You did good.

1:24:08.878 --> 1:24:11.879
[instrumental music]

1:24:17.086 --> 1:24:18.986
[birds chirping]

1:24:18.988 --> 1:24:20.988
[engine revving]

1:24:20.990 --> 1:24:23.957
[music continues]

1:24:36.005 --> 1:24:37.237
[sighs]

1:24:49.385 --> 1:24:52.352
[engine revving]

1:24:57.693 --> 1:25:00.661
[dramatic music]

1:25:11.373 --> 1:25:14.441
Hey, everybody, work quickly
but cleanly.

1:25:14.443 --> 1:25:16.076
Okay, he's gonna be
sitting there.

1:25:16.078 --> 1:25:17.644
I want to be able to see
the expressions on his face

1:25:17.646 --> 1:25:20.481
I want to be able
to see his hands on the coke.

1:25:20.483 --> 1:25:23.650
Suspect's in red vehicle heading
north towards highway five.

1:25:23.652 --> 1:25:25.119
[engine revving]

1:25:25.121 --> 1:25:27.121
[dramatic music]

1:25:50.079 --> 1:25:52.379
What are you up to, John?

1:26:00.923 --> 1:26:02.523
You didn't actually
rebuild that car

1:26:02.525 --> 1:26:04.591
on your father's lawn, did you?

1:26:06.695 --> 1:26:08.595
No.

1:26:08.597 --> 1:26:10.697
If I so much as stepped
on daddy's lawn

1:26:10.699 --> 1:26:13.200
he'd have beaten six shades
of shit out of me.

1:26:15.004 --> 1:26:17.070
Too bad. I like that story.

1:26:18.807 --> 1:26:22.142
My father was
a born again alcoholic.

1:26:22.144 --> 1:26:24.711
He made everyone's life
a misery.

1:26:27.783 --> 1:26:29.116
You want me to tell them that?

1:26:31.353 --> 1:26:34.354
History is written
by the victors.

1:26:35.491 --> 1:26:37.090
I will be remembered.

1:26:38.661 --> 1:26:40.727
My car will be remembered.

1:26:42.298 --> 1:26:45.265
Our skuzzy coke deal will not.

1:26:49.638 --> 1:26:50.871
Ping-pong.

1:26:52.641 --> 1:26:54.041
[John chuckles]

1:26:56.645 --> 1:26:58.045
Ping-pong.

1:27:00.849 --> 1:27:02.449
[knocking on door]

1:27:03.252 --> 1:27:04.585
Ellen!

1:27:04.587 --> 1:27:05.819
[panting]

1:27:07.823 --> 1:27:09.623
Cristina:
I know you're in there.

1:27:10.826 --> 1:27:12.593
Open the door!

1:27:15.264 --> 1:27:16.863
We have to talk.

1:27:16.865 --> 1:27:19.833
[instrumental music]

1:27:20.936 --> 1:27:22.936
[engine revving]

1:27:26.775 --> 1:27:28.408
Come on!

1:27:35.684 --> 1:27:37.651
[drill whirring]

1:27:41.523 --> 1:27:44.491
[music continues]

1:27:45.961 --> 1:27:47.794
Dammit! Now, what?

1:27:53.702 --> 1:27:55.135
Great.

1:27:59.875 --> 1:28:02.442
- John.
- What the fuck's he doing here?

1:28:02.444 --> 1:28:04.878
Where are you going, John?
Open the window, Jim.

1:28:04.880 --> 1:28:06.580
Open the window, Jim. Jim!

1:28:06.582 --> 1:28:08.949
- What do you want me to do?
- Do what you have to do.

1:28:08.951 --> 1:28:12.386
Come on, Jim.
You fuckin' piece of shit.

1:28:12.388 --> 1:28:13.954
Hey, what the...
Get your hands off me.

1:28:13.956 --> 1:28:15.389
- You're coming with us.
- I know my rights.

1:28:15.391 --> 1:28:17.624
[indistinct chatter]

1:28:17.626 --> 1:28:19.293
Benedict: Well, just make sure
you've got him

1:28:19.295 --> 1:28:20.661
head to toe in there.

1:28:20.663 --> 1:28:22.229
Lift the glass up, please.

1:28:22.231 --> 1:28:24.197
[indistinct chatter]

1:28:26.135 --> 1:28:28.969
I've got the champagne.

1:28:28.971 --> 1:28:30.804
Has this been bugged yet?

1:28:30.806 --> 1:28:33.473
So, what are you gonna do
if something goes wrong?

1:28:33.475 --> 1:28:36.643
It won't.
John always has a plan.

1:28:36.645 --> 1:28:39.579
I've been down this road before
and I love Jim,

1:28:39.581 --> 1:28:41.248
I'm never gonna leave him

1:28:41.250 --> 1:28:43.116
but if John
is just your golden ticket

1:28:43.118 --> 1:28:44.618
then you need to have
a plan 'cause you will be

1:28:44.620 --> 1:28:46.586
dragged down with him.

1:28:49.258 --> 1:28:51.658
[phone ringing]

1:28:52.995 --> 1:28:54.461
- Jim?
- Ellen, it's Bill.

1:28:54.463 --> 1:28:55.762
I'm looking for John,
do you have any idea

1:28:55.764 --> 1:28:57.497
where he is or Cristina or--

1:28:57.499 --> 1:28:59.766
- Has something happened?
- No. What do you mean?

1:28:59.768 --> 1:29:01.802
- What could've happened?
- No, nothing. Sorry, Bill.

1:29:01.804 --> 1:29:05.205
- No, I don't know where--
- Oh, let me talk to him.

1:29:05.207 --> 1:29:06.840
Give me the phone!

1:29:07.776 --> 1:29:09.343
Bill.

1:29:09.345 --> 1:29:11.545
Cristina, it's absolutely vital
that I speak to John

1:29:11.547 --> 1:29:13.113
immediately,
we know he's in LA

1:29:13.115 --> 1:29:16.083
but we can't find him.
You know where he is?

1:29:17.853 --> 1:29:20.854
[dramatic music]

1:29:26.995 --> 1:29:29.963
[indistinct chatter]

1:29:37.039 --> 1:29:38.205
Thank you.

1:29:39.475 --> 1:29:42.209
Well, you're moments away

1:29:42.211 --> 1:29:44.077
from being a very rich man.

1:29:44.079 --> 1:29:45.746
<i> Howard: Okay, let me rephrase</i>
<i> the question.</i>

1:29:45.748 --> 1:29:48.815
Who first raised the subject
of a possible drug deal?

1:29:48.817 --> 1:29:51.418
It's hard to say.
It just kind of came up.

1:29:51.420 --> 1:29:53.186
H-- how did it just "come up?"

1:29:53.188 --> 1:29:56.390
Well, one minute it wasn't there
and the next minute, it was.

1:29:56.392 --> 1:29:58.024
- Hurry up, come on.
- They're in the lobby.

1:29:58.026 --> 1:29:59.259
Heading upstairs.
Let's get everything ready.

1:29:59.261 --> 1:30:00.894
Okay. Got it.

1:30:00.896 --> 1:30:02.929
Agent 1: Hide that,
hide that. Go.

1:30:02.931 --> 1:30:05.432
[intense music]

1:30:09.037 --> 1:30:12.406
Mr. DeLorean, excuse me, sir.
Is it, Mr. DeLorean?

1:30:13.575 --> 1:30:14.908
I have a call for you, sir.

1:30:16.745 --> 1:30:19.913
I'll transfer the call to the
house phone, right over there.

1:30:19.915 --> 1:30:22.749
So did he-- he just call you
and-- and-- and say,

1:30:22.751 --> 1:30:24.851
"Hey, man, I need $30 million

1:30:24.853 --> 1:30:28.288
to save my company,
let's do a drug deal?"

1:30:28.290 --> 1:30:30.424
<i> Jim: What are we talking</i>
<i> about here, John?</i>

1:30:32.728 --> 1:30:34.127
That I need help.

1:30:34.129 --> 1:30:36.196
It's just not cut
and dry like you want.

1:30:36.198 --> 1:30:37.597
I-- I-- it really isn't.

1:30:37.599 --> 1:30:40.133
That's v-- very different
than suggesting

1:30:40.135 --> 1:30:42.402
a-- a-- drug deal,
don't you think?

1:30:42.404 --> 1:30:43.970
Well, it is and it isn't.

1:30:43.972 --> 1:30:45.939
He may have alluded to it.

1:30:45.941 --> 1:30:49.910
You don't think
that Thomas Edison...

1:30:49.912 --> 1:30:51.912
or Ford or Kennedy didn't cut
a few corners

1:30:51.914 --> 1:30:54.014
every now and then
for the greater good?

1:30:55.417 --> 1:30:57.317
Is any of this alluding
to be found

1:30:57.319 --> 1:30:59.920
in the many hours of FBI tapes

1:30:59.922 --> 1:31:02.489
of your phone calls
with Mr. DeLorean?

1:31:02.491 --> 1:31:04.124
Uh, no. This predates that.

1:31:05.928 --> 1:31:07.160
John DeLorean.

1:31:07.162 --> 1:31:08.261
John, we have a deal

1:31:08.263 --> 1:31:09.563
to save the car, the factory...

1:31:09.565 --> 1:31:11.798
- Everything.
- Bill.

1:31:11.800 --> 1:31:13.400
Bill: Minit Financial came
through with a 100 million

1:31:13.402 --> 1:31:15.635
but you need
to sign it now, today,

1:31:15.637 --> 1:31:17.103
before the Brits get wind of it

1:31:17.105 --> 1:31:18.738
or there'll be no company
left to save.

1:31:18.740 --> 1:31:22.142
- I have a deal here.
Bill: No, you don't.

1:31:22.144 --> 1:31:24.311
You have a life sentence.

1:31:24.313 --> 1:31:25.979
You need to sign this.

1:31:25.981 --> 1:31:27.981
[instrumental music]

1:31:27.983 --> 1:31:30.317
- I can't do it, Bill.
- Why, for Christ sake?

1:31:30.319 --> 1:31:32.285
This is what we've been breakin'
our asses for.

1:31:32.287 --> 1:31:34.354
Because they'll own the company.

1:31:35.791 --> 1:31:37.023
At best,
I'll be a figure head

1:31:37.025 --> 1:31:39.659
and most likely
they'll push me out.

1:31:39.661 --> 1:31:41.761
Bill: You can't just throw it
all away like this!

1:31:43.298 --> 1:31:46.099
So, basically,
what it all comes down to

1:31:46.101 --> 1:31:48.268
is your word against his.

1:31:48.270 --> 1:31:51.104
The word of a man
who even according to you

1:31:51.106 --> 1:31:55.609
is one of the most respected
businessmen in the world.

1:31:55.611 --> 1:31:58.011
And that of a drug smuggler

1:31:58.013 --> 1:31:59.980
and government informant.

1:31:59.982 --> 1:32:02.949
[dramatic music]

1:32:09.391 --> 1:32:10.857
Okay, we've got
about 30 seconds.

1:32:10.859 --> 1:32:12.392
[indistinct chatter]

1:32:14.796 --> 1:32:16.296
Benedict: Come on.

1:32:16.298 --> 1:32:19.566
You know
the biggest mistake we made?

1:32:19.568 --> 1:32:22.736
[exhales] Making all the cars
the same color.

1:32:22.738 --> 1:32:25.705
Sure, they're futuristic
looking but...

1:32:25.707 --> 1:32:27.474
should've had a variety.

1:32:27.476 --> 1:32:29.676
Once we secure the company,
we're going to come out

1:32:29.678 --> 1:32:30.977
with a whole range of colors

1:32:30.979 --> 1:32:33.914
and it's going to be amazing.

1:32:33.916 --> 1:32:35.549
Are you okay, John?

1:32:36.351 --> 1:32:38.151
[sighs] Sure.

1:32:40.889 --> 1:32:43.723
You know, I never thanked you
properly, Jim,

1:32:43.725 --> 1:32:45.725
and I always meant to.

1:32:50.032 --> 1:32:51.498
W... Hey...

1:32:53.001 --> 1:32:54.568
[intense music]

1:32:56.505 --> 1:32:57.904
Don't do this, John.

1:32:58.941 --> 1:33:01.074
Just go home to Cristina.

1:33:01.076 --> 1:33:03.209
Work somethin' else out.

1:33:03.211 --> 1:33:04.778
I'll go in here alone and just

1:33:04.780 --> 1:33:07.347
call the whole thing off,
alright?

1:33:07.349 --> 1:33:09.316
No, you're missing the point.

1:33:10.786 --> 1:33:14.087
John DeLorean always leads
from the front.

1:33:14.089 --> 1:33:16.089
That's why he's John DeLorean.

1:33:17.559 --> 1:33:20.860
Right?
Everything's gonna be fine.

1:33:20.862 --> 1:33:22.829
[knocking on door]

1:33:35.711 --> 1:33:37.811
John, glad you could make it.

1:33:37.813 --> 1:33:40.213
- This is John Vicenza.
- Hello. Alright.

1:33:41.717 --> 1:33:43.817
- Heard a lot about you, John.
Vicenza: Hi.

1:33:43.819 --> 1:33:45.251
Vicenza: Kind of a different
world for you, huh?

1:33:45.253 --> 1:33:49.289
Well, you'd be surprised.

1:33:49.291 --> 1:33:52.425
I, uh, took the opportunity
of ordering some champagne.

1:33:52.427 --> 1:33:56.830
Well, [chuckles] it, it seems
like a day for champagne, huh?

1:34:01.303 --> 1:34:02.969
Benedict: Now...

1:34:02.971 --> 1:34:04.471
[DeLorean chuckles]

1:34:10.579 --> 1:34:14.447
Um, are the, uh,

1:34:14.449 --> 1:34:16.516
are the, uh, monkeys here?

1:34:16.518 --> 1:34:17.984
[chuckles] Some.

1:34:17.986 --> 1:34:20.120
Uh, the rest are downstairs.

1:34:20.122 --> 1:34:21.588
John: Mm-hm.

1:34:24.259 --> 1:34:27.227
[dramatic music]

1:34:35.504 --> 1:34:36.770
Oh!

1:34:36.772 --> 1:34:39.739
[laughing]

1:34:41.877 --> 1:34:43.877
We got a quite a party here.

1:34:49.151 --> 1:34:51.451
It's, uh...

1:34:53.455 --> 1:34:55.121
Go ahead, John.

1:34:58.026 --> 1:34:59.359
Pick it up.

1:34:59.361 --> 1:35:02.362
[dramatic music]

1:35:26.822 --> 1:35:28.688
Well, that's better than gold.

1:35:28.690 --> 1:35:31.257
Gold weighs more than that,
for goodness sakes.

1:35:31.259 --> 1:35:32.659
[both laughing]

1:35:34.396 --> 1:35:38.264
So, here's to, uh,
to a lot of success for everyone

